      <description>&lt;p&gt;Step 1: Open Settings in Windows 11&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Step 2: Go to Apps&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Step 3: Go to Advanced app settings&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Step 4: Go to App execution aliases&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Step 5: Disable the option for python.exe and python3.exe&lt;/p&gt;</description>
